The paper deals with the problem of recovering sparse, correlated, time-varying signals from sub-Nyquist, non-adaptive, linear measurements, which is a problem in signal processing. Therefore, cs.SP (Signal Processing) is a likely category. The paper also proposes a probabilistic dynamic CS signal model and an approximate message passing algorithm, which are related to information theory and machine learning, respectively. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.MM (Multimedia) are also likely categories. Finally, the paper applies the proposed algorithm to real dynamic CS datasets, which involves practical applications and could fall under cs.SI (Systems and Control).
